snippet.textDisplay: Don't forget that the people that 'fixed' Sonic were all fired because Paramount and Disney (for Lion King) combined didn't pay them enough to stay open so the parent company closed them.  They have the opportunity to move to another location but they likely won't get anything extra for any bonuses sent to the company. Everyone seems to be on a tirade about seeing it because they finally listened to fans, but fail to look at the full picture: Paramount didn't redesign sonic, the Sonic Team didn't design the new sonic, in fact they both agreed to the ugly design; Sega's indie team at Sonic Mania provided the art and redesigns from their artist, MPC Vancouver remade all the scenes, and now fans are throwing money at a company that allowed 400 to 800 jobs be taken from the market.
snippet.textOriginal: Don't forget that the people that 'fixed' Sonic were all fired because Paramount and Disney (for Lion King) combined didn't pay them enough to stay open so the parent company closed them.  They have the opportunity to move to another location but they likely won't get anything extra for any bonuses sent to the company. Everyone seems to be on a tirade about seeing it because they finally listened to fans, but fail to look at the full picture: Paramount didn't redesign sonic, the Sonic Team didn't design the new sonic, in fact they both agreed to the ugly design; Sega's indie team at Sonic Mania provided the art and redesigns from their artist, MPC Vancouver remade all the scenes, and now fans are throwing money at a company that allowed 400 to 800 jobs be taken from the market.

snippet.textDisplay: 2:41 He does know that the rings act as portals in the original sonic games, right? I mean, he played through Sonic Mania. With each character. For a total of 3 times. How does he not remember that. You'd enter the giant rings and play the bonus game to collect a chaos emerald. Obviously, they haven't brought chaos emeralds into the cinematic lore (yet?), but ring portals were a thing in the first Sonic the Hedgehog.
